		<div class="row content-text">
			<a id="getting-started"></a>
			<h3 class="help-header">Getting Started &nbsp; <span class="fa fa-paper-plane-o fa-fw fa-1x i-navy help-small-sq" ></span> </h3>
			<p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q1.</span> What is GeoGem?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> GeoGem is a web application that collects and analyzes behavioral data for students with autism.<br>
				The program was created by computer science students at <a href="http://www.noctrl.edu">North Central College</a>. 
				You can read more at the <%= link_to "About", about_path %>.
			</p>
			
			<hr class="help-line">
			
			<p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q2. My Home page doesn’t have any students? What do I do?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span>Students are assigned by your school’s Admin users. You should ask them to assign
				students to your roster so that you can begin your work.
			</p>
			
			<hr class="help-line">
			
            <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q3.</span> I’m lost! How do I get back to the Home page?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> Select GeoGem in the upper right of the screen to return Home.
			</p>
			
			<hr class="help-line">
			<p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q4.</span> Uh-oh. I forgot my password. What now?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> Contact your school’s Admin user. He or she can reset your password.
			</p>
            <hr class="help-line">
            <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q5.</span> Can I change my password?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> Yes. Select Profile at the top of the screen.
				The Change Password icon is at the bottom of your profile. 
			</p>
            <hr class="help-line">
            <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q6.</span> How do I change my username? I’d prefer to login with my email.
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> Sorry. Once you have a username, it can’t be changed. Not even by your Admin.
			</p>
			<!-- end getting started questions -->
            <hr class="help-line">
            <!-- Sessions questions -->
			<a id="sessions"></a>
			<h3 class="help-header">Sessions &nbsp;  <span class="fa fa-key fa-fw fa-1x i-red help-small-sq" ></span></h1>
			<p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q7.</span> Why does my Home page only show 8 student icons? I have more than 8 students.
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A. The student icons are the last 8 students you worked with.You can always see all your student in the
				“Student:” dropdown below the icons.
			</p>
			
			<hr class="help-line">
			<p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q8.</span> What do the different behavior squares mean?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A. There are three types of behavior squares:
									<ol type="1">
  <li>Frequency squares have a lightning bolt. They simply increment each time they are pressed.</li>
  <li>Duration squares have a timer. These squares track the length of an event. Select the square to start the timer. And select again to stop it.</li>
  <li>Interval squares have a bullseye or concentric circles. These squares are like frequency squares, they increment. But during analysis, the counts are only shown per interval: showing whether the square pressed during an interval or not.</li>
</ol> 
			</p>
            <hr class="help-line">
            <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q9.</span> During a session, if I mistakenly press a button, can I undo it?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> Yes. Select the red Undo button in the lower right to undo. 
				You can only undo the last square pressed, not more than that. 
			</p>
			<!-- end sessions questions -->
            <hr class="help-line">
            <!-- Admin powers questions-->
            <a id="admin-powers"></a>
			<h3 class="help-header">Admin Powers &nbsp;  <span class="fa fa-trophy fa-fw fa-1x i-yellow help-small-sq" ></span></h1>
			<p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q10.</span> I’m overwhelmed. Where do I start?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> Select Admin at the top of the page. This will take you to the Admin Dashboard.
				You’ll usually start from here. There are three “things” in GeoGem: Students, Teachers, and Squares.
				From the Admin Dashboard, you’ll define your school by creating and editing your Students, Teachers, and Squares.
			</p>
            <hr class="help-line">
            <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q11.</span> How can I remove a remove a teacher or student from the system? 
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> There is no way to completely remove a Teacher (or Student or Square) from GeoGem.
			</p>
			<hr class="help-line">
			<p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q12.</span> Wait. I can’t remove a teacher? Well, what if someone leaves the school?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A. Good point! While you can’t remove the teacher (and the session data associated with that teacher),
				you CAN suspend the login for any teacher. Here are the steps: 
									<ol type="1">
			  <li>Goto the Admin Dashboard,</li>
			  <li>Select All Teachers,</li>
			  <li>Select the teacher,</li>
			  <li>Select the Login Setting action icon at the bottom,</li>
			  <li>Set Login Status to “Suspended” and then “Change Settings”. </li>
			</ol> 
			<span class="help-qa-letter">After this, your suspended teacher will not be able to login to GeoGem.
			
			</p>
            <hr class="help-line">
             <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q13.</span>I created a teacher and some students. But now, that teacher can’t
				access any of the students. What can I do? 
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> From the Admin Dashboard, select All Teachers. From there, select 
				the teacher you want to change. At the bottom of that teacher’s profile page, select the Student Roster icon.
				That page will allow you to add or remove students from a teacher’s roster.
			</p>
			<hr class="help-line">
			 <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q14.</span> So, teachers can only access students in their roster.
				Ok. As an Admin, which students can I access?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span>Correct. Teachers can only access students in their roster.
				These students are assigned by you, the Admin. Second, an Admin can always access any student in the school.
			</p>
			<hr class="help-line">
			 <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q15.</span> One of my teachers forgot his GeoGem password. How can I fix this problem?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span>Here’s the sequence: Goto the Admin Dashboard; Select All Teachers;
				Select the teacher you want; Select the Login Settings action icon at the bottom of the page. From there,
				you can reset a teacher’s password. Also in Login Settings, you can change a teacher’s powers
				(Admin, Teacher, or SessionOnly), or even suspend a teacher’s login.
			</p>
			<hr class="help-line">
			 <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q16.</span> What are the differences between the three Teacher “powers” settings?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> There are three power levels for teachers (from strongest to weakest):
				Admin, Teacher, and SessionOnly. An Admin can create and edit nearly everything for their school in GeoGem.
				This is the person in charge. Teacher powers include running behavioral sessions and also analyzing the results.
				SessionOnly users can only run behavioral sessions and not analysis reports. The intent is that aides or volunteers
				would be candidates for SessionOnly status.
			</p>
			<hr class="help-line">
			 <p>
				<span class="help-qa-letter">Q17.</span> I see how I can change the password of other teachers, but as an Admin,
				how do I change my own password? And my gosh… what if I forget MY password? What then?
			</p>
			<p class="help-answer-para">
				<span class="help-qa-letter">A:</span> Select Profile in the navbar at the top of the page. That will take you to
				your Profile Page. At the bottom, you’ll see the Change Password action icon. Go there to change your own password. 
				If you forget your password and there isn’t another Admin in your school, then you need to contact GeoGem’s Super User for help.
				The best course is to email Prof Bill at
				<a href="mailto:wtkrieger@noctrl.edu">wtkrieger@noctrl.edu</a>.
			<!--End Admin powers questions-->
			</p>
			<hr class="help-line">
			
